1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:01:33,190
♪

2
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,180
Since Sir Okubo's murder
by Shishio's henchmen,

3
00:01:38,180 --> 00:01:39,260
a lot has happened.

4
00:01:39,260 --> 00:01:42,140
Makoto Shishio met
a long-lost nemesis,

5
00:01:42,140 --> 00:01:44,280
Aoshi Shinomori, the
head of the Oni gang

6
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:46,230
and asked him to
join his group.

7
00:01:46,230 --> 00:01:49,200
But Aoshi refused and went
to Kyoto to kill Kenshin

8
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,290
While walking to Edo,

9
00:01:50,290 --> 00:01:53,070
Kenshin encountered a
robbery in progress.

10
00:01:53,070 --> 00:01:58,020
♪

11
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:59,270
I'd say you might
as well just give up

12
00:01:59,270 --> 00:02:02,120
because there's no way
you'll escape my robbing you.

13
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:04,210
Stand and deliver.

14
00:02:04,210 --> 00:02:07,250
Just be calm
and give me--

15
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:09,280
(boinging noise)

16
00:02:11,180 --> 00:02:13,080
Sorry, but I have no money.

17
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,200
(audible sigh)

18
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:16,070
With the kind of rags
this guy is wearing,

19
00:02:16,070 --> 00:02:17,050
I believe it.

20
00:02:17,050 --> 00:02:19,010
So what happened, did
your wife leave you?

21
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:21,100
Huh, I've never
been married!

22
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:23,110
Well, I'm not surprised.

23
00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:25,130
Ooh, nice sword.

24
00:02:25,130 --> 00:02:27,230
I'll let you live but you
must hand over your sword.

25
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:29,050
But this is
all I've got!

26
00:02:29,050 --> 00:02:31,020
A sword like that
must be worth a lot,

27
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:33,020
you know, they've become
quite rare since the decree

28
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:35,270
made them illegal, so
hand it over, poor boy!

29
00:02:35,270 --> 00:02:37,030
Huh?

30
00:02:37,030 --> 00:02:40,020
(shouting)

31
00:02:40,020 --> 00:02:43,100
♪

32
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:46,040
(shouting)

33
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,210
I got ya!

34
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:51,020
Oh, was that a punch?

35
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:52,130
I can't believe
you weren't broken

36
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:55,020
completely in two by
my attack, what gives?

37
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,250
Well, you're not the
best at using leverage,

38
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,040
and you don't have
much body weight

39
00:02:58,040 --> 00:02:59,210
so it just
wasn't effective.

40
00:02:59,210 --> 00:03:00,290
(growling)

41
00:03:00,290 --> 00:03:02,190
Well, I was
just warming up.

42
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:05,260
That was just a
suck-you-in punch, boy.

43
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:09,210
(shouting)

44
00:03:09,210 --> 00:03:15,200
♪

45
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,230
Oh!

46
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:19,070
(shrieking)

47
00:03:19,070 --> 00:03:21,280
(grunting)

48
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:23,050
(shrieking)

49
00:03:23,050 --> 00:03:25,240
Stop trying to dodge my
power, you gutless guy!

50
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:28,010
Uh, sorry, I was
trained that way.

51
00:03:28,010 --> 00:03:30,230
(grunting)

52
00:03:30,230 --> 00:03:32,270
(yelling)

53
00:03:32,270 --> 00:03:34,290
Oh.

54
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:36,220
(grunting)

55
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:38,140
Whoo, I think
you dropped this,

56
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:39,100
is this your money?

57
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,040
Huh, oh.

58
00:03:42,130 --> 00:03:43,190
Yes, it is!

59
00:03:43,190 --> 00:03:47,130
Now you will die!

60
00:03:47,130 --> 00:03:51,060
You fool, no one
can survive Hikumo.

61
00:03:51,060 --> 00:03:53,130
(screaming)

62
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:56,050
♪

63
00:03:56,050 --> 00:03:57,250
Ahh!

64
00:03:57,250 --> 00:04:00,030
That's my cloak!

65
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:02,180
Uh oh, now I've
really done it.

66
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:04,190
Give me that back now.

67
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:06,070
I saw you take
this bag of money

68
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:07,200
from those men
you knocked out,

69
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:09,240
and it's only right that it
should be returned to them

70
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,160
because it's theirs.

71
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:14,130
You're wrong,
now give it here!

72
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:15,260
They stole it
from someone else

73
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:19,120
so I earned it, now you
got the whole story, do you?

74
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,170
Now here's your choice,

75
00:04:20,170 --> 00:04:21,270
you're either gonna
give me the money

76
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:24,060
or give me your sword
so what ya gonna do?

77
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:26,240
All right.

78
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:28,220
That's more like it.

79
00:04:28,220 --> 00:04:31,000
I hope the
blade's not rusted.

80
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,230
Oh, what are you doing
with a reverse-edged sword?

81
00:04:33,230 --> 00:04:36,220
Nobody wants a reverse-edged
sword, it's not worth a yen,

82
00:04:36,220 --> 00:04:38,190
but it's the only thing
in the world I cherish

83
00:04:38,190 --> 00:04:40,120
so why don't you just
give it back to me?

84
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,040
Hmm.

85
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:43,040
Hmm.

86
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,150
Well, you wrecked
my favorite cloak

87
00:04:44,150 --> 00:04:46,180
so I guess it's only fair
I get to keep your sword.

88
00:04:46,180 --> 00:04:49,050
Ah, but I've had
that sword for years!

89
00:04:49,050 --> 00:04:50,090
Please!

90
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:51,100
Well, I had
this for years

91
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:53,020
and, thanks to you,
it's worthless.

92
00:04:53,020 --> 00:04:54,060
Here you go!

93
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:56,040
Okay, I've been holding
out on you, here,

94
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:58,180
you can have all my money,
just give me back my sword!

95
00:04:58,180 --> 00:05:00,250
Really, ha!

96
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:02,180
Great!

97
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:07,010
Aw, there's not enough here
to even pay attention.

98
00:05:07,010 --> 00:05:09,210
Well, it's become obvious to
me that you and these hoods

99
00:05:09,210 --> 00:05:12,130
are not the rightful owners
of this bag of money.

100
00:05:12,130 --> 00:05:13,170
So what?

101
00:05:13,170 --> 00:05:15,030
So, I'm gonna
return this

102
00:05:15,030 --> 00:05:16,200
to whoever it
really belongs to.

103
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,250
Hey, hey, hey, wait up!

104
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:19,060
Let's talk this over.

105
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:22,030
(grunting)

106
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:25,070
She'll pay for this.

107
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:28,250
(dog barking)

108
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:33,190
The Odawara Inn
and Money Exchange.

109
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:36,030
Well then, this
must be the place.

110
00:05:36,030 --> 00:05:37,110
It's locked.

111
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:38,120
Pretty quiet
around here,

112
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,190
they don't even
seem to realize

113
00:05:39,190 --> 00:05:40,260
they've been robbed.

114
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:43,010
They'll be pleased that
we returned this to them.

115
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:44,240
(grunting)

116
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:52,260
So am I supposed to be
impressed or something?

117
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:53,280
I can tell
by that move

118
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:56,250
you're a thief as
well, Mister Honesty.

119
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:59,290
Whatever you are,
get ready, I'm coming!

120
00:05:59,290 --> 00:06:02,200
(yelling)

121
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,180
Whoa!

122
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:11,040
(grunting)

123
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,230
Ha!

124
00:06:12,230 --> 00:06:14,080
From the way she
made that jump,

125
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:16,260
I'd say she studied
Kenpo and Tang Soo Do.

126
00:06:16,260 --> 00:06:18,160
She must have had some
excellent senseis

127
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:20,100
to do that as
well as she did.

128
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,200
And the way
she's dressed,

129
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:24,070
her tight little body
is making my blood boil.

130
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:25,230
Don't give
yourself eye strain.

131
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:26,280
Oh.

132
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:32,030
I can't believe this,
these people are loaded.

133
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:34,170
Well, it's certainly easy
to see why they got robbed.

134
00:06:34,170 --> 00:06:36,090
They leave their
safe wide open.

135
00:06:36,090 --> 00:06:38,160
There, well, now that
that's taken care of,

136
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,230
I guess I can--huh?

137
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:40,250
I've hit the jackpot.

138
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:42,110
Oh!

139
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:44,170
I know being in here
must be very tempting

140
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:46,290
for a person like you, but
you just have to resist.

141
00:06:46,290 --> 00:06:48,120
But how's a poor
girl like me

142
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,150
gonna get all the way
to Edo without money?

143
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:52,200
-Uh, Edo?
-Yeah, Edo,

144
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,230
what's the big deal?

145
00:06:53,230 --> 00:07:05,220
♪

146
00:07:07,130 --> 00:07:09,100
(water lapping)

147
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:15,030
That's interesting, I'm
headed for Edo myself.

148
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:17,140
So, I guess your home
is in Edo, right?

149
00:07:17,140 --> 00:07:20,020
Right, I had to go to Kyoto
to check something out,

150
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:21,250
but, unfortunately,
I've run out of money

151
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:23,080
on the way back home.

152
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:25,240
Why would a girl like you
want to go to Kyoto alone?

153
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,150
I'm just curious.

154
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:29,170
Well, I'll tell you, I
was looking for someone

155
00:07:29,170 --> 00:07:31,200
who was a very important
person in my life.

156
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,050
I was orphaned as a baby

157
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:35,000
and this person took
me under his wing.

158
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,280
He raised me as if I
was his own daughter.

159
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:40,060
This was a long time ago,
just after the Tokugawa Era.

160
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:42,030
We lived in
a large group.

161
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:43,200
They were all very kind.

162
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,100
So the reason you went
to Kyoto was to look

163
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:46,220
for your stepfather?

164
00:07:46,220 --> 00:07:49,150
Yes, when I was 11, we
were traveling through Edo

165
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:51,120
and he decided
to leave me there.

166
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,160
Are you telling me
he deserted you?

167
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:55,220
No, he left me in
the care of an old man

168
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:57,240
because the police
were chasing him.

169
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,040
He was the best,

170
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,080
and I know someday
I'll find him.

171
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:03,280
Until we're reunited, I'll
keep searching for him,

172
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:06,070
but I gotta go back
home to earn more money.

173
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:09,030
♪

174
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:11,140
So I was in Kyoto
trying to find him.

175
00:08:11,140 --> 00:08:13,200
But I went broke before
I could locate him.

176
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,020
I'm sure that if
you stick to it,

177
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:17,270
you'll find him someday,
Miss--what's your name?

178
00:08:17,270 --> 00:08:19,110
Misao.

179
00:08:19,110 --> 00:08:23,010
My name is Misao Makimachi.

180
00:08:23,010 --> 00:08:25,260
But it's okay if
you call me Misao.

181
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:27,270
Ms. Misao, I know
you need money,

182
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:29,200
but I'm sure you know
just how wrong it is

183
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,180
to steal it from others.

184
00:08:31,180 --> 00:08:33,070
You don't have
the slightest idea

185
00:08:33,070 --> 00:08:35,020
what it's like to have
to eat grass for weeks

186
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:37,070
because you don't have
any money to eat real food.

187
00:08:37,070 --> 00:08:38,180
When you've tried
a steady diet

188
00:08:38,180 --> 00:08:40,210
of caterpillars,
cockroaches, frogs...

189
00:08:40,210 --> 00:08:42,140
Why don't you use
the money I gave you

190
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:46,080
to write your old
man friend in Edo...

191
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,180
What a good idea!

192
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:49,100
(thudding)

193
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,230
(audible sigh)

194
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:51,290
You know those guys
you knocked out

195
00:08:51,290 --> 00:08:53,030
are probably angry.

196
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:54,150
I wouldn't be
a bit surprised

197
00:08:54,150 --> 00:08:56,010
if they're out right
now looking for you

198
00:08:56,010 --> 00:08:57,240
and that bag of loot
you took from them.

199
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,130
They could be yakuza.

200
00:08:59,130 --> 00:09:00,200
And no matter
who they are,

201
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:01,290
you better leave town
before they find you--

202
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,020
There's that bitch!

203
00:09:03,020 --> 00:09:04,130
-Hey!
-Let's get her!

204
00:09:04,130 --> 00:09:06,170
Yeah!

205
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:07,290
Now you've had it!

206
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:10,260
No one gets away with
what you tried to do to us!

207
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:13,080
Give us your money!

208
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,100
♪

209
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:17,040
And even then,
we're gonna kill ya!

210
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,240
(laughing)

211
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:21,170
Well, here goes nothing.

212
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:23,060
We're completely surrounded.

213
00:09:23,060 --> 00:09:24,250
I'm sorry that I
put you in this jam,

214
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:26,220
but now I could
really use your help.

215
00:09:26,220 --> 00:09:28,120
Get 'em, boys!

216
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:36,030
♪

217
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:38,160
All right, I'll help.

218
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,030
Listen, I'll give
all of you one chance

219
00:09:40,030 --> 00:09:41,140
to leave us alone.

220
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:42,240
Huh?

221
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:44,240
(shouting)

222
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:47,200
♪

223
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,190
I'd say, "You two
haven't got a chance."

224
00:09:49,190 --> 00:09:51,030
It's all over for you.

225
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:53,120
♪

226
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,290
(gasping)

227
00:09:54,290 --> 00:09:57,120
You guys stole that loot
and this girl robbed you.

228
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,170
I'd say all of you
made a big mistake.

229
00:09:59,170 --> 00:10:01,060
So here's what
you should do.

230
00:10:01,060 --> 00:10:02,150
All of you should
give this up

231
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:04,120
and let's just
call things even.

232
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,180
(grumbling)

233
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:08,180
(cracking)

234
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:11,150
(yelling)

235
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,270
My--oh!

236
00:10:17,270 --> 00:10:20,150
(water lapping)

237
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:30,000
You know, I'm not sure
you're much of a fighter,

238
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,180
but your wit
certainly served us

239
00:10:31,180 --> 00:10:32,290
well on that bridge.

240
00:10:32,290 --> 00:10:35,250
Well, years ago, I was in
many battles on bridges.

241
00:10:35,250 --> 00:10:38,260
What I just did was pretty
much second nature to me.

242
00:10:38,260 --> 00:10:40,220
You have to know
that kind of a bridge.

243
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:42,050
You have to know
it's supported

244
00:10:42,050 --> 00:10:44,000
and what's stressed when
it's got weight on it.

245
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,160
When all those
men got closer,

246
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:47,260
it was easy to cut it,
making it collapse.

247
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:49,260
Hmm.

248
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:51,240
The man who raised me
had a group of guys

249
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:53,090
around him that
were amazing.

250
00:10:53,090 --> 00:10:55,040
They were great
martial artists.

251
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,250
So let's hear
all about 'em.

252
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:58,280
He and his men
guarded Edo Castle

253
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,270
during the disturbance

254
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:01,290
at the end of
the Tokugawa Era.

255
00:11:01,290 --> 00:11:05,180
♪

256
00:11:05,180 --> 00:11:07,080
Ah.

257
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,230
His name's Aoshi Shinomori.

258
00:11:09,230 --> 00:11:11,260
I wonder just where
he and his Oni gang

259
00:11:11,260 --> 00:11:14,100
are tonight under
the full moon.

260
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:18,020
♪

261
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:19,260
Shinomori, Aoshi?

262
00:11:19,260 --> 00:11:22,080
Huh?

263
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:24,160
(wind howling)

264
00:11:26,070 --> 00:11:28,210
(water lapping)

265
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:33,230
What do you know
about Aoshi?

266
00:11:33,230 --> 00:11:35,170
So do you know him?

267
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:36,210
Tell me, where are they?

268
00:11:36,210 --> 00:11:37,220
Is he doing well?

269
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:41,000
Just when is the last
time you saw Aoshi anyway?

270
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,070
(giggling)

271
00:11:42,070 --> 00:11:44,050
You must be old friends.

272
00:11:44,050 --> 00:11:57,110
♪

273
00:11:57,110 --> 00:11:59,190
Kyoto, Battousai,

274
00:11:59,190 --> 00:12:01,230
I'll have my revenge.

275
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:03,200
(birds chirping)

276
00:12:10,180 --> 00:12:12,250
So you haven't exactly
been very talkative

277
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:14,010
since I brought up Aoshi.

278
00:12:14,010 --> 00:12:16,090
I have to think from your
silence that deep down,

279
00:12:16,090 --> 00:12:18,130
you're jealous of Aoshi
and the fighting skills

280
00:12:18,130 --> 00:12:22,170
of his Oni gang, so don't be
a spoilsport about this.

281
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:24,290
I got it, someone in his
gang must have given you

282
00:12:24,290 --> 00:12:26,120
an old-fashioned
butt whipping.

283
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,140
It was probably Han'nya,
he's great at Kenpo

284
00:12:28,140 --> 00:12:30,260
and really kicking
guys' butts.

285
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:32,050
Hey!

286
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:34,220
Where you going, Mr. Redhead
Fred Rag-Picker Jones,

287
00:12:34,220 --> 00:12:36,260
Mr. The Martial Artist
Formerly Known As

288
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:40,210
Mr. X Marks The
Scar On My Face!

289
00:12:40,210 --> 00:12:42,060
In case you're
interested, Misao,

290
00:12:42,060 --> 00:12:44,010
my real name is
Kenshin Himura.

291
00:12:44,010 --> 00:12:46,070
If you could, please
call me by my real name.

292
00:12:46,070 --> 00:12:48,050
So you mean if I call
you by your real name,

293
00:12:48,050 --> 00:12:50,200
you might fill me in
on my long-lost friends?

294
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,190
Calling by my real name
should have nothing to do

295
00:12:52,190 --> 00:12:53,210
with that other issue.

296
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:56,060
Oh, Kenshin.

297
00:12:56,060 --> 00:12:57,090
Ya!

298
00:12:57,090 --> 00:12:59,230
I guess this is
another issue, too!

299
00:12:59,230 --> 00:13:01,200
(moaning)

300
00:13:03,230 --> 00:13:05,170
All right, I want
you to cut the crap

301
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:07,240
and spill your guts!

302
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:09,230
Oh, stop running away!

303
00:13:11,030 --> 00:13:12,200
I can't give
up on this.

304
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:15,200
I really feel that
he knows something.

305
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:17,180
This is the first time
in all of my searching

306
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:20,270
that I've met someone who
might actually know Aoshi.

307
00:13:20,270 --> 00:13:23,200
(birds chirping)

308
00:13:29,130 --> 00:13:31,100
(clanging)

309
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:43,100
Hmm?

310
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:45,120
Kenshin, we've got
to get under a tree,

311
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:47,080
it's gonna rain!

312
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:49,180
(thundering)

313
00:13:52,050 --> 00:13:54,190
(raining)

314
00:14:02,090 --> 00:14:04,030
It's a good thing
the Oni gang taught me

315
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:05,110
how to read weather.

316
00:14:10,030 --> 00:14:13,170
Just think, we'll be
in Edo in one more day.

317
00:14:13,170 --> 00:14:15,070
Boy, looks like rain.

318
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:16,140
Yeah.

319
00:14:16,140 --> 00:14:17,200
This is a big storm,

320
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:20,120
I wonder if Kenshin's getting
soaked by this rainstorm.

321
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:22,160
I remember a time when
we were all together

322
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:24,280
and got stuck in a
thunderous rainstorm.

323
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,290
♪

324
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:31,200
Kori, hurry up, will ya?

325
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:33,290
Gosh, the rain's just
really coming down,

326
00:14:33,290 --> 00:14:36,060
it's a real downpour.

327
00:14:36,060 --> 00:14:37,130
It's like a flash flood.

328
00:14:37,130 --> 00:14:39,230
My new kimono is
completely soaked.

329
00:14:39,230 --> 00:14:41,130
It'll be all right.

330
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:46,230
♪

331
00:14:46,230 --> 00:14:47,240
(audible sigh)

332
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:50,180
♪

333
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:52,140
Oh, Kenshin.

334
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:12,110
So you feel like
talking, Kenshin?

335
00:15:12,110 --> 00:15:13,180
Sure.

336
00:15:13,180 --> 00:15:15,180
Well, we don't have
to talk about Aoshi

337
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:17,100
if you don't
want to, okay?

338
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:19,040
Aoshi.

339
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:21,190
But as a dad, he did a
fine job of raising me.

340
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:23,090
I feel like he was
the greatest dad

341
00:15:23,090 --> 00:15:24,220
a girl could ever have.

342
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:26,130
You know Aoshi
was so smart,

343
00:15:26,130 --> 00:15:27,270
he was the head
of the Oni gang

344
00:15:27,270 --> 00:15:29,120
when he was just 15.

345
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,250
And under his leadership,
we all flourished.

346
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:34,210
He always had a strong
sense of responsibility.

347
00:15:34,210 --> 00:15:37,070
And even though he rarely
showed his true feelings,

348
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:39,270
he was always very
caring towards me.

349
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:42,000
I lived with him
for nine years

350
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,200
and even I never
saw him smile

351
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,260
except for just one time.

352
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:47,270
I'll never forget it,
he captured someone

353
00:15:47,270 --> 00:15:49,100
that tried to betray him.

354
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:51,100
He had the
man executed.

355
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:52,260
But I bet when
he sees me again

356
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:54,230
after all these years,
he'll have a big smile

357
00:15:54,230 --> 00:15:55,280
on his face for me!

358
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:57,140
Hey, where the
hell are you going?

359
00:15:57,140 --> 00:15:59,030
The rain stopped
so I'm off to Edo.

360
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:00,200
Then wait for me!

361
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:03,190
(birds chirping)

362
00:16:03,190 --> 00:16:07,220
♪

363
00:16:07,220 --> 00:16:09,080
Maybe I should tell
her about what happened

364
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:11,040
to Aoshi and his Oni gang.

365
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:13,190
Then again, the news
would probably crush her.

366
00:16:13,190 --> 00:16:16,160
After all, we want to
see our dreams fulfilled.

367
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:18,070
Maybe it's better to
let her keep her dream

368
00:16:18,070 --> 00:16:19,290
of seeing him again.

369
00:16:19,290 --> 00:16:20,240
On the other hand,

370
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,270
she has such a
distorted view of Aoshi.

371
00:16:22,270 --> 00:16:25,000
She actually
thinks he was nice.

372
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,280
Maybe to her he was.

373
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:29,290
Besides, Aoshi and his
gang are all dead now.

374
00:16:29,290 --> 00:16:31,160
What's the point in
destroying her image

375
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,140
of a man who
cared for her?

376
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:35,250
She's not gonna stop
asking about it though.

377
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:37,110
I think the best
way to handle this

378
00:16:37,110 --> 00:16:38,250
is to lose her.

379
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:40,210
Hey!

380
00:16:40,210 --> 00:16:41,250
Wait up!

381
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:45,140
So you think you
can escape from me.

382
00:16:45,140 --> 00:16:47,170
Well, not only did I
grow up in the Oni gang,

383
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:49,050
but the trained me in
the art of stalking

384
00:16:49,050 --> 00:16:50,070
and now you're my prey,

385
00:16:50,070 --> 00:16:52,010
so you can run,
but you can't hide.

386
00:16:52,010 --> 00:16:54,100
So come out, crawl out
wherever you are, Kenshin.

387
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:55,190
Chicken!

388
00:16:55,190 --> 00:16:57,160
(boinging)

389
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,260
(growling)

390
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:02,250
(grunting)

391
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:05,180
(panting)

392
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:13,020
♪

393
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:14,020
She wasn't kidding.

394
00:17:14,020 --> 00:17:16,030
Miss Misao runs
as fast as a deer,

395
00:17:16,030 --> 00:17:17,100
I can't lose her.

396
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:18,240
She must really
want some answers

397
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,210
about what
happened to Aoshi.

398
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:23,120
Hey!

399
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:25,000
Damn, I'm having
a hell of a time

400
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,020
keeping up
with this guy.

401
00:17:26,020 --> 00:17:28,130
I gotta stay with him.

402
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:30,090
This Kenshin is
something else.

403
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:32,100
I wonder if he and Aoshi
ever fought each other,

404
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:34,020
and, if so, what happened?

405
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:35,270
I guess--whoa!

406
00:17:35,270 --> 00:17:38,070
Oh!

407
00:17:38,070 --> 00:17:40,190
All right, where
the hell'd you go?

408
00:17:44,140 --> 00:17:47,040
Our little game of
cat and mouse is over.

409
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:49,080
I'll be the one who says
if and when we're through

410
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:50,042
with each other.

411
00:17:50,042 --> 00:17:51,230
Now you're in trouble!

412
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:53,220
(grunting)

413
00:17:53,220 --> 00:17:55,060
(gasping)

414
00:17:55,060 --> 00:17:56,150
Oh.

415
00:17:58,080 --> 00:18:01,190
♪

416
00:18:08,210 --> 00:18:10,060
You have got
to be kidding.

417
00:18:10,060 --> 00:18:12,210
There is no way he
could've jumped this canyon.

418
00:18:12,210 --> 00:18:14,170
Is there?

419
00:18:14,170 --> 00:18:16,050
Well, I've got
to do something.

420
00:18:16,050 --> 00:18:19,000
I can't let a man with so
many answers just get away.

421
00:18:21,090 --> 00:18:23,110
Well, you can't
get away from me!

422
00:18:23,110 --> 00:18:25,230
(whooshing)

423
00:18:25,230 --> 00:18:29,060
(exploding)

424
00:18:29,060 --> 00:18:30,230
Huh?

425
00:18:30,230 --> 00:18:33,080
He created air pressure
that stopped my hikimu

426
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:36,020
from even reaching him.

427
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:37,180
You need to
go back home.

428
00:18:37,180 --> 00:18:39,220
Leave me alone and
get on with your life.

429
00:18:39,220 --> 00:18:41,160
(gasping)

430
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:43,280
♪

431
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:46,020
I wish I could tell you
something about Aoshi

432
00:18:46,020 --> 00:18:47,090
but the truth is,

433
00:18:47,090 --> 00:18:48,170
I never met the man.

434
00:18:48,170 --> 00:18:50,080
I had just heard
stories about him.

435
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:53,280
I'm sorry if I
got your hopes up.

436
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:56,030
But you shouldn't feel
bad about him leaving you.

437
00:18:56,030 --> 00:18:57,190
He probably loved
you very much

438
00:18:57,190 --> 00:18:59,030
and didn't want to
see you get hurt.

439
00:18:59,030 --> 00:19:00,230
That's why he left
you with the old man,

440
00:19:00,230 --> 00:19:02,060
he knew the life
of a gangster.

441
00:19:02,060 --> 00:19:04,030
It's a sad life that
almost always ends

442
00:19:04,030 --> 00:19:06,190
in an early
death or prison.

443
00:19:06,190 --> 00:19:08,200
♪

444
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:11,010
I know what it's like
having a burning emptiness

445
00:19:11,010 --> 00:19:14,100
in your heart that can only
be put out by a loved one.

446
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,170
But sometimes we
have no choice

447
00:19:17,170 --> 00:19:19,240
but to live
without them.

448
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:28,060
♪

449
00:19:28,060 --> 00:19:29,150
I wish you well.

450
00:19:29,150 --> 00:19:31,050
I never give up.

451
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:33,150
(shouting)

452
00:19:33,150 --> 00:19:37,020
♪

453
00:19:37,020 --> 00:19:38,260
You really think you
can get off that easy?

454
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:40,290
Well, I've got news
for you, Kenshin.

455
00:19:40,290 --> 00:19:42,270
The Oni gang
never quits.

456
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:45,070
(grunting)

457
00:19:46,230 --> 00:19:47,190
No!

458
00:19:47,190 --> 00:19:49,160
Don't try it, Misao!

459
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:51,170
How can you even think
I could live with myself

460
00:19:51,170 --> 00:19:52,120
the rest of my life

461
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:54,140
if I didn't at
least try to do it?

462
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:56,060
Huh?

463
00:19:56,060 --> 00:19:58,280
(shouting)

464
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:05,170
♪

465
00:20:05,170 --> 00:20:07,200
(yelling)

466
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,040
(screaming)

467
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:15,050
♪

468
00:20:15,050 --> 00:20:18,220
(shouting)

469
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:20,080
(exploding)

470
00:20:21,230 --> 00:20:23,180
Now I understand.

471
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:25,170
Kenshin must've
known Aoshi.

472
00:20:25,170 --> 00:20:27,270
He probably became a
part of the Oni gang

473
00:20:27,270 --> 00:20:30,040
after they left
me in Kyoto.

474
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:32,140
He must know
where they are.

475
00:20:32,140 --> 00:20:36,010
Now I can finally relax
knowing all my years

476
00:20:36,010 --> 00:20:39,190
of emptiness will
soon come to an end.

477
00:20:39,190 --> 00:20:47,140
♪

478
00:20:47,140 --> 00:20:49,050
Oh my!

479
00:20:49,050 --> 00:20:51,060
What happened,
was I knocked out?

480
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:53,280
Uh huh.

481
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:55,150
Misao, I want
you to promise

482
00:20:55,150 --> 00:20:59,030
that's the last time you'll
ever do anything that crazy.

483
00:20:59,030 --> 00:21:00,130
I promise.

484
00:21:00,130 --> 00:21:01,210
I just couldn't
stand the thought

485
00:21:01,210 --> 00:21:03,250
of not knowing the
truth about Aoshi.

486
00:21:03,250 --> 00:21:05,030
And wherever
you're going,

487
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:06,200
I'm going to
go with you.

488
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,130
I just want you to
know ahead of time,

489
00:21:08,130 --> 00:21:10,230
there are some pretty vicious
people that are after me.

490
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:12,000
You might be
risking your life

491
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,180
just traveling with me.

492
00:21:14,180 --> 00:21:16,230
But if you're willing
to accept that risk,

493
00:21:16,230 --> 00:21:19,180
I'd consider it an honor
to have your company.

494
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:23,070
Okay, Kenshin,
you've got a deal.

495
00:21:23,070 --> 00:21:24,270
I'm not afraid!

496
00:21:24,270 --> 00:21:27,130
And on the way to Edo,
you can tell me all about

497
00:21:27,130 --> 00:21:30,210
what really happened
between you and Aoshi.

498
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:33,060
Ugh, don't you
ever give up?

499
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:34,160
No way!

500
00:21:36,290 --> 00:23:13,270
♪

